[geoip] replace requirements.txt with Pipfile

Pipfile (used by pipenv) is the new and recommended way to handle python
dependencies. This change was brought on in part by a security warning from
github about a security issue in the version of the requests library that we
were using.

Pipfile makes it easier to upgrade to newer versions of the libraries used.

This change is reflected in the infrastructure repo as well, where pipenv is
used to install the geoip dependencies.

Chrome (and all browsers based on Blink) cache content based on urls
only. Meta urls can be requested with different content types so the
wrong types can get cached.
This commit adds a dummy parameter so the browser cache can
differenciate html and json urls.
